Libya Rebels Say Qaddafi Can Stay If He Resigns, Reuters Says

-- B y   M a r i a m   F a m
-- 
2011-07-03T14:41:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-03/libya-rebels-say-qaddafi-can-stay-if-he-resigns-reuters-says.html
The head of  Libya ’s rebel National
Transitional Council said Libyan leader Muammar Qaddafi can stay
in the country as long as he resigns and there is international
supervision of his movements, Reuters  reported .  Mustafa Abdul Jalil also said Qaddafi must order his
soldiers to withdraw from their positions, the news agency said.  Abdul Jalil said he made the offer about a month ago
through a United Nations envoy and hasn’t yet received an
answer, Reuters said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariam Fam in Cairo at 
 mfam1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 